WEBVTT

00:02.719 --> 00:05.038
Okay, so get this. The
kids brushed their teeth

00:05.063 --> 00:06.295
and went straight to bed.

00:06.297 --> 00:08.564
I think somebody replaced
'em with Pod People.

00:09.534 --> 00:10.907
I mean, I'm gonna miss 'em,

00:10.932 --> 00:12.765
but I am not complaining.

00:14.050 --> 00:16.071
You're welcome.

00:16.627 --> 00:18.263
Oh, you're taking credit for this?

00:18.288 --> 00:19.153
Yes, I am.

00:19.155 --> 00:20.588
Because after school today,

00:20.590 --> 00:22.089
your kids were out of control.

00:22.091 --> 00:24.205
Our living room was
like the first 15 minutes

00:24.230 --> 00:25.793
of Saving Private Ryan.

00:26.996 --> 00:29.597
Okay, so they're my kids
when they do something wrong?

00:29.599 --> 00:32.366
Yeah, or when they're in a school play.

00:32.368 --> 00:33.868
Yeah, three hours

00:33.870 --> 00:36.204
of watching Emme be a
tree in The Wizard of Oz.

00:36.206 --> 00:37.371
The witch said, "I'm melting."

00:37.373 --> 00:39.073
I was like, "Take me with you."

00:41.678 --> 00:44.612
That's like Club Med compared
to what I dealt with today.

00:44.614 --> 00:45.980
While I was on the phone with a client,

00:45.982 --> 00:48.516
the kids decided to have
a Nerf dart shootout.

00:48.518 --> 00:51.652
Katie nails me in the face, right?

00:51.654 --> 00:54.021
And I open my mouth
in surprise, as you do.

00:54.023 --> 00:56.657
Right? Teddy rolls by on his skateboard

00:56.659 --> 00:59.360
and shoots one down my throat.

01:00.196 --> 01:01.562
I coughed up the foam part,

01:01.564 --> 01:04.632
but the rubber tip is
still inside me somewhere.

01:04.634 --> 01:05.774
Oh, honey.

01:05.837 --> 01:07.137
Yeah, well, it won't happen again

01:07.139 --> 01:08.371
because I handled it.

01:08.373 --> 01:10.371
The way you kids behaved today

01:10.396 --> 01:12.705
was completely unacceptable, okay?

01:12.730 --> 01:14.730
So from now on, there will be no

01:14.732 --> 01:17.166
skateboards, no Nerf wars,

01:17.168 --> 01:20.206
no monkey business in the house.

01:20.231 --> 01:22.065
What's a monkey's business?

01:23.508 --> 01:25.107
It's an old person word for fun.

01:25.109 --> 01:26.642
He's trying to ban fun.

01:26.644 --> 01:29.378
That's exactly right, Katie.

01:29.380 --> 01:31.013
I'm banning fun.

01:31.876 --> 01:35.518
So until further notice, all of these...

01:35.520 --> 01:37.353
will go in the off-limits cubby.

01:37.355 --> 01:38.893
No!

01:38.918 --> 01:41.056
All right, get in there.

01:45.630 --> 01:47.930
I really wish that had a door on it.

01:48.458 --> 01:50.399
God, I wonder why they were so wound up?

01:51.669 --> 01:53.066
Oh, you know what? It rained today

01:53.091 --> 01:54.336
so they didn't have recess.

01:54.338 --> 01:55.905
That always makes 'em a little crazy.

01:55.907 --> 01:58.908
They seemed fine after
school at the ice cream place.

02:00.745 --> 02:02.243
You took 'em for ice cream?

02:02.268 --> 02:04.380
Yeah, well, you know I like ice cream.

02:04.382 --> 02:06.749
And if I want to eat
it, I got buy them some.

02:08.550 --> 02:09.884
What difference does it make?

02:09.887 --> 02:12.054
I'm just trying to figure
out why they were so nuts.

02:12.079 --> 02:12.873
Well, it doesn't matter why.

02:12.898 --> 02:14.233
- I handled it.
- Okay,

02:14.258 --> 02:16.839
but you didn't take
everything into consideration.

02:16.864 --> 02:17.893
Look,

02:17.895 --> 02:18.961
different situations

02:18.963 --> 02:20.296
require different reactions.

02:20.298 --> 02:21.664
Like if it were me,

02:21.666 --> 02:22.998
I would have taken 'em to the park,

02:23.000 --> 02:24.133
let 'em run it out.

02:24.135 --> 02:26.835
You know, like dogs.

02:30.074 --> 02:31.907
Nah.

02:31.909 --> 02:33.509
Yelling and taking stuff away,

02:33.511 --> 02:35.978
that's my move.

02:36.279 --> 02:37.745
Okay, but...

02:37.770 --> 02:38.914
now that you're home with the kids more,

02:38.916 --> 02:41.450
you might want to expand your playbook.

02:41.452 --> 02:42.751
I don't think so.

02:42.753 --> 02:43.919
I have one move.

02:43.921 --> 02:45.407
My dad had one move.

02:45.432 --> 02:47.699
My dad's dad had one move.

02:47.799 --> 02:49.365
And that one move

02:49.390 --> 02:50.990
won two world wars.

02:52.296 --> 02:54.196
Trust me, we didn't take the Germans

02:54.198 --> 02:55.998
to the park and let 'em run it out.

02:58.822 --> 03:01.916
I'm telling you, if you
put two round hot tubs

03:01.941 --> 03:03.482
at the end of a long pool,

03:03.507 --> 03:04.974
from the second story balcony,

03:04.976 --> 03:06.342
you're gonna get a very...

03:06.344 --> 03:09.578
masculine view.

03:09.580 --> 03:10.746
If you know what I'm sayin'.

03:10.748 --> 03:13.282
Yeah. Yeah, okay.

03:13.498 --> 03:14.741
I will take care of it.

03:14.766 --> 03:15.718
All right, bye.

03:15.720 --> 03:17.486
Gee.

03:17.488 --> 03:18.954
- Hey.
- Hey, how was your day?

03:18.956 --> 03:19.721
How were the kids?

03:19.746 --> 03:21.023
They were fantastic.

03:21.025 --> 03:22.958
Listen to the sound...

03:22.960 --> 03:24.493
of silence.

03:25.829 --> 03:26.762
Huh?

03:26.764 --> 03:28.744
My one move... the perfect move...

03:28.769 --> 03:29.798
is still working.

03:29.800 --> 03:31.500
In fact, it's so good, I named it:

03:31.502 --> 03:32.901
The Velvet Hammer.

03:34.829 --> 03:36.162
Um,

03:36.187 --> 03:37.987
isn't that the name of the gay bar

03:38.012 --> 03:40.145
by the ice cream shop?

03:41.316 --> 03:43.646
It doesn't matter where
the name came from.

03:45.263 --> 03:46.860
That's what I'm calling it.

03:47.461 --> 03:48.314
Mm-kay, well,

03:48.339 --> 03:50.052
- good for you, honey. 
- Mm-kay.

03:51.055 --> 03:52.388
What was that?

03:52.390 --> 03:53.922
I don't know, but it better not be fun.

